<TITLE> 20-30m to turn refugees: FM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 9 (bdnews24.com)  Foreign Minister Dipu Moni said on Wednesday Bangladeshis will constitute half of the people displaced by climate change globally. "This (climate change) will raise human tragedy, poverty and the number of slum dwellers in the cities. We should prepare to face the problems," she said at a book publication ceremony at the Dhaka University. Dipu Moni said the catastrophe will render 20-30 million people homeless in Bangladesh. Among the others, University Grants Commission chairman professor Nazrul Islam and Dhaka University pro vice-chancellor Dr. Harun-ar Rashid spoke on the occasion. bdnew
